And here we are on this amazing,
gorgeous, beautiful planet.

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:34.110 align:middle line:84%
The planet is undergoing
massive amounts of impact

00:09:34.110 --> 00:09:36.960 align:middle line:84%
from human culture
and from pollution,

00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:40.530 align:middle line:84%
from the way that we're
running our technologies.

00:09:40.530 --> 00:09:44.400 align:middle line:84%
And when we look at the
thinking and the minds

00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:46.500 align:middle line:84%
of so many of the
people on the planet,

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:50.340 align:middle line:84%
we realize that because
of the American way

00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:52.506 align:middle line:90%
or because of whatever--

00:09:52.506 --> 00:09:53.306 align:middle line:90%
this is--

00:09:53.306 --> 00:09:55.110 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or the
Chinese way, whatever.

00:09:55.110 --> 00:09:57.510 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: The Chinese way,
whatever you want to call it.

00:09:57.510 --> 00:09:58.320 align:middle line:90%
You've got school.

00:09:58.320 --> 00:09:59.010 align:middle line:90%
You've got work.

00:09:59.010 --> 00:09:59.910 align:middle line:90%
You've got to do this thing.

00:09:59.910 --> 00:10:00.900 align:middle line:90%
You got to make this money.

00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:01.740 align:middle line:90%
You've got a thing.

00:10:01.740 --> 00:10:02.850 align:middle line:84%
And then you've
got to make enough.

00:10:02.850 --> 00:10:03.808 align:middle line:90%
And you go buy a house.

00:10:03.808 --> 00:10:05.190 align:middle line:90%
And you-- all this.

00:10:05.190 --> 00:10:08.310 align:middle line:84%
Our minds are conditioned
into these very small

00:10:08.310 --> 00:10:09.660 align:middle line:90%
little streams.

00:10:09.660 --> 00:10:12.780 align:middle line:84%
And we suddenly realize we've
lost the freedom of thinking

00:10:12.780 --> 00:10:15.960 align:middle line:84%
and choice to be able to
make decisions that are

00:10:15.960 --> 00:10:17.860 align:middle line:90%
going to be good for everyone.

00:10:17.860 --> 00:10:20.210 align:middle line:90%
And so why do we need guardians?

00:10:20.210 --> 00:10:22.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, we need guardians
to reflect back to people

00:10:22.710 --> 00:10:24.300 align:middle line:90%
and say, well, you know what?

00:10:24.300 --> 00:10:29.850 align:middle line:84%
You're not perhaps seeing the
full impact of the choices

00:10:29.850 --> 00:10:31.050 align:middle line:90%
that you're making.

00:10:31.050 --> 00:10:34.440 align:middle line:84%
But if you were willing
to look at these pieces,

00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:37.560 align:middle line:84%
you might be able to see
that this is creating harm

00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:39.360 align:middle line:90%
or this is creating good.

00:10:39.360 --> 00:10:43.770 align:middle line:84%
And so protecting the
destiny of the human race,

00:10:43.770 --> 00:10:46.960 align:middle line:84%
protecting the children
for generations to come,

00:10:46.960 --> 00:10:48.720 align:middle line:84%
that is the role
of the guardian.

00:10:48.720 --> 00:10:52.110 align:middle line:84%
The guardian is not there to
make decisions for anyone,

00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:55.560 align:middle line:84%
but instead to empower
the consciousness

00:10:55.560 --> 00:10:58.470 align:middle line:84%
to be able to see the
potential future that we

00:10:58.470 --> 00:11:01.140 align:middle line:84%
can have in which we're
thriving, and happy,

00:11:01.140 --> 00:11:02.100 align:middle line:90%
and abundant.

00:11:02.100 --> 00:11:03.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can the
individual be a guardian?

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:05.520 align:middle line:90%
Or must it be the masses?

00:11:05.520 --> 00:11:08.640 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: I think every
individual has a responsibility

00:11:08.640 --> 00:11:11.100 align:middle line:90%
to be a guardian to some extent.

00:11:11.100 --> 00:11:14.860 align:middle line:84%
Not every individual will
choose that responsibility.

00:11:14.860 --> 00:11:18.000 align:middle line:84%
And so we need people
who are willing to take

00:11:18.000 --> 00:11:20.730 align:middle line:84%
that responsibility
and to stand forward

00:11:20.730 --> 00:11:22.998 align:middle line:84%
for those future generations
and for our planet.

00:11:22.998 --> 00:11:24.165 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You're a physicist.

00:11:24.165 --> 00:11:24.600 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: I am a physicist.

00:11:24.600 --> 00:11:26.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is the
unified theory of physics?

00:11:26.820 --> 00:11:27.620 align:middle line:90%
What's that mean?

00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:30.390 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: Yeah,
so I do this work

00:11:30.390 --> 00:11:33.030 align:middle line:84%
since I was a
teenager that I call

00:11:33.030 --> 00:11:35.040 align:middle line:90%
the unified harmonic matrix.

00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:37.740 align:middle line:84%
And it emerged from
a vision in which

00:11:37.740 --> 00:11:40.002 align:middle line:84%
I saw the interconnectedness
of everything.

00:11:40.002 --> 00:11:40.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: As a teenager?

00:11:40.960 --> 00:11:41.385 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: As a teenager.

00:11:41.385 --> 00:11:42.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's remarkable.

00:11:42.540 --> 00:11:47.040 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: And I started
doing deep dives into physics

00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:50.610 align:middle line:84%
in order to see if
somehow there were

00:11:50.610 --> 00:11:54.870 align:middle line:84%
keys to this whole
unified theory that

00:11:54.870 --> 00:11:58.000 align:middle line:84%
was emerging from inside of me
inside of the existing physics

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:58.800 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:11:58.800 --> 00:12:02.790 align:middle line:84%
And mainly, what I found was a
lot of scattered puzzle pieces

00:12:02.790 --> 00:12:04.150 align:middle line:90%
that hadn't been put together.

00:12:04.150 --> 00:12:05.442 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Fragmented everywhere.

00:12:05.442 --> 00:12:08.880 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: And all of the
cracks, all the fragments

00:12:08.880 --> 00:12:13.200 align:middle line:84%
were basically the pieces that
were missing this understanding

00:12:13.200 --> 00:12:16.650 align:middle line:84%
of this fundamental field,
what we may call the ether,

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:20.190 align:middle line:90%
or the vital force, prana, chi.

00:12:20.190 --> 00:12:22.168 align:middle line:84%
You go to any
mystery tradition--

00:12:22.168 --> 00:12:24.210 align:middle line:84%
and this is what I did as
a teenager when I first

00:12:24.210 --> 00:12:25.500 align:middle line:90%
discovered this--

00:12:25.500 --> 00:12:28.290 align:middle line:84%
and all of these different
mystery traditions

00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:30.690 align:middle line:84%
are all talking
about this field.

00:12:30.690 --> 00:12:33.100 align:middle line:84%
And yet, it was
completely missing

00:12:33.100 --> 00:12:35.490 align:middle line:84%
in what I was seeing
was modern physics.

00:12:35.490 --> 00:12:37.680 align:middle line:84%
And I eventually realized
that it was actually

00:12:37.680 --> 00:12:41.203 align:middle line:84%
cut out of physics around
the turn of the 1900s.

00:12:41.203 --> 00:12:43.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're familiar with
the work of physicist Nassim

00:12:43.620 --> 00:12:44.470 align:middle line:90%
Haramein.

00:12:44.470 --> 00:12:44.620 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: I am.

00:12:44.620 --> 00:12:44.780 align:middle line:90%
He's a good friend.

00:12:44.780 --> 00:12:46.320 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: He's a good guy.

00:12:46.320 --> 00:12:48.150 align:middle line:10%
We have a Gaia
documentary that he's

00:12:48.150 --> 00:12:50.940 align:middle line:10%
been included in called
"Black Hole," where

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:54.570 align:middle line:10%
he talks about this
theory of unified physics.

00:12:54.570 --> 00:12:55.894 align:middle line:10%
>>APOLLO: That's right.

