00:14:16.180 --> 00:14:18.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
think of Einstein, Adam?

00:14:18.140 --> 00:14:20.540 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: There's
something about Einstein

00:14:20.540 --> 00:14:22.160 align:middle line:90%
that most people don't know.

00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:25.460 align:middle line:84%
When he published his theory
on special relativity,

00:14:25.460 --> 00:14:29.690 align:middle line:84%
it supposedly wiped out the
need for the luminiferous

00:14:29.690 --> 00:14:36.080 align:middle line:84%
either, this sort of
more metaphysical basis

00:14:36.080 --> 00:14:38.120 align:middle line:84%
for the arising
of all forces that

00:14:38.120 --> 00:14:41.020 align:middle line:84%
was known for thousands of
years if you go into the vast.

00:14:41.020 --> 00:14:42.830 align:middle line:84%
Michelson and
Morley's experiment

00:14:42.830 --> 00:14:44.880 align:middle line:84%
supposedly proved
it didn't exist,

00:14:44.880 --> 00:14:47.360 align:middle line:84%
although all they had
was a tabletop laser.

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:49.760 align:middle line:84%
And they were trying
to detect if you

00:14:49.760 --> 00:14:53.750 align:middle line:84%
could feel the ether
moving through the laser

00:14:53.750 --> 00:14:55.790 align:middle line:84%
as it's spinning
around the Earth.

00:14:55.790 --> 00:14:57.980 align:middle line:84%
And of course, they weren't
thinking about the fact

00:14:57.980 --> 00:15:01.970 align:middle line:84%
that maybe the ether is moving
with the surface of the Earth.

00:15:01.970 --> 00:15:04.460 align:middle line:84%
And then Einstein
supposedly disproved it.

00:15:04.460 --> 00:15:06.270 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
thing you know,

00:15:06.270 --> 00:15:08.570 align:middle line:90%
he releases general relativity.

00:15:08.570 --> 00:15:12.560 align:middle line:84%
And in general relativity,
he's describing spacetime

00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:14.220 align:middle line:90%
as a fabric.

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:18.620 align:middle line:84%
And as that fabric warps and
weaves, light goes with it.

00:15:18.620 --> 00:15:20.540 align:middle line:84%
And it was his teacher
Lorenz who came to him,

00:15:20.540 --> 00:15:22.730 align:middle line:84%
and he said, Einstein,
you know you just

00:15:22.730 --> 00:15:25.820 align:middle line:90%
prove the ether exists, right?

00:15:25.820 --> 00:15:28.040 align:middle line:90%
And he's like, oy, you're right.

00:15:28.040 --> 00:15:31.490 align:middle line:84%
And so he does this
whole paper on the ether.

00:15:31.490 --> 00:15:35.870 align:middle line:84%
And in it, he says, you cannot
have the theory of general

00:15:35.870 --> 00:15:38.150 align:middle line:90%
relativity without an ether.

00:15:38.150 --> 00:15:42.000 align:middle line:84%
Spacetime must have fundamental
mechanical qualities.

00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:42.800 align:middle line:90%
But you know what?

00:15:42.800 --> 00:15:43.760 align:middle line:90%
Everybody ignored it.

00:15:43.760 --> 00:15:44.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Why?

00:15:44.560 --> 00:15:46.280 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: Nobody publicized it.

00:15:46.280 --> 00:15:47.470 align:middle line:84%
Scientists still to this
day don't talk about it.

00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:49.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They didn't accept it?

00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:52.345 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: Because somehow this
association with the ether--

00:15:52.345 --> 00:15:53.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is he right?

00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:56.070 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: --associated
it with spirituality.

00:15:56.070 --> 00:15:57.270 align:middle line:90%
And he was right.

00:15:57.270 --> 00:15:59.170 align:middle line:90%
Spacetime is an ether.

00:15:59.170 --> 00:16:00.170 align:middle line:90%
And that's what it is.

00:16:00.170 --> 00:16:03.470 align:middle line:84%
It's literally a
fundamental fabric woven

00:16:03.470 --> 00:16:06.600 align:middle line:90%
of what I call a light lattice.

00:16:06.600 --> 00:16:11.120 align:middle line:84%
It's a high tensegrity
lattice made of light.

00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:12.783 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is
vacuum catastrophe?

00:16:12.783 --> 00:16:15.200 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: The vacuum catastrophe
is something Nassim talks

00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:17.150 align:middle line:90%
about a lot.

00:16:17.150 --> 00:16:21.830 align:middle line:84%
It's a point in the mid
1900s where basically we

00:16:21.830 --> 00:16:24.260 align:middle line:84%
were using two
plates to see if we

00:16:24.260 --> 00:16:28.260 align:middle line:84%
could measure how much energy
is in completely empty space.

00:16:28.260 --> 00:16:30.050 align:middle line:84%
And what we found
was that there's

00:16:30.050 --> 00:16:33.410 align:middle line:84%
such a gargantuanly
large amount of energy

00:16:33.410 --> 00:16:36.350 align:middle line:84%
there that physicists
couldn't explain it.

00:16:36.350 --> 00:16:38.890 align:middle line:84%
And they had to re-normalize
all the equations.

00:16:38.890 --> 00:16:40.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They can't
seem to explain much.

00:16:40.820 --> 00:16:43.280 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: No, it's true.

00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:45.510 align:middle line:84%
To be fair, there's a lot
of really great physicists

00:16:45.510 --> 00:16:46.310 align:middle line:90%
out there.

00:16:46.310 --> 00:16:50.090 align:middle line:10%
And when I was in
high school, the work

00:16:50.090 --> 00:16:52.730 align:middle line:10%
of Lee Smolin on
loop quantum gravity

00:16:52.730 --> 00:16:56.510 align:middle line:10%
helped me to gain some
traction and understanding that

00:16:56.510 --> 00:16:59.450 align:middle line:10%
spacetime itself is a
geometric structure.

00:16:59.450 --> 00:17:01.400 align:middle line:90%
But he was missing--

00:17:01.400 --> 00:17:05.329 align:middle line:84%
their form of spacetime-- and
we see this a lot in magazines

00:17:05.329 --> 00:17:06.260 align:middle line:90%
these days--

00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:09.319 align:middle line:84%
this kind of wobbly,
foamy spacetime

00:17:09.319 --> 00:17:11.089 align:middle line:90%
that's just all crazy.

00:17:11.089 --> 00:17:13.460 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, this is not
the way it actually looks.

00:17:13.460 --> 00:17:17.270 align:middle line:84%
It's got to have some kind
of pattern or geometry.

00:17:17.270 --> 00:17:19.790 align:middle line:84%
Because everything that
we see arising around us,

00:17:19.790 --> 00:17:24.560 align:middle line:84%
from plants, to animals, to the
pattern of the galaxy flowing--

00:17:24.560 --> 00:17:27.250 align:middle line:84%
all of these things have
fundamental geometric patterns

00:17:27.250 --> 00:17:28.050 align:middle line:90%
inside them.

00:17:28.050 --> 00:17:31.240 align:middle line:84%
The fire ratio, and
the hexagonal lattice,

00:17:31.240 --> 00:17:33.240 align:middle line:90%
and all of these things.

00:17:33.240 --> 00:17:35.840 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought,
well, what would

00:17:35.840 --> 00:17:39.110 align:middle line:84%
make the most sense is if
everything was triangular

00:17:39.110 --> 00:17:42.200 align:middle line:84%
and if there was a natural
balance in the triangular

00:17:42.200 --> 00:17:44.300 align:middle line:90%
structure of space.

00:17:44.300 --> 00:17:47.030 align:middle line:84%
And I started thinking
about how space permeates.

00:17:47.030 --> 00:17:48.260 align:middle line:90%
What would make it flat?

00:17:48.260 --> 00:17:51.350 align:middle line:84%
What would make it curve
and make gravity happen?

00:17:51.350 --> 00:17:53.090 align:middle line:90%
What would make it spin?

00:17:53.090 --> 00:17:55.130 align:middle line:84%
And I started working
out the fundamentals

00:17:55.130 --> 00:17:57.470 align:middle line:84%
of how gravity and
curvature happen

00:17:57.470 --> 00:18:00.440 align:middle line:84%
through these pentagonal
intersections.

00:18:00.440 --> 00:18:05.510 align:middle line:84%
Spacetime equilibrium happens
through a hexagonal lattice.

00:18:05.510 --> 00:18:09.580 align:middle line:84%
And spin happens through this
sort of seven pointed lattice.

00:18:09.580 --> 00:18:12.710 align:middle line:84%
And some time into
that exploration,

00:18:12.710 --> 00:18:14.930 align:middle line:84%
I came across Buckminster
Fuller's work.

00:18:14.930 --> 00:18:15.730 align:middle line:90%
And I realized--

00:18:15.730 --> 00:18:17.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The geodesic dome?

00:18:17.420 --> 00:18:18.680 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: That's right.

00:18:18.680 --> 00:18:21.290 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that
Bucky absolutely

00:18:21.290 --> 00:18:25.400 align:middle line:84%
had all these basic geometric
permutations worked out.

00:18:25.400 --> 00:18:29.510 align:middle line:84%
And he even defined
the fundamental sort

00:18:29.510 --> 00:18:32.360 align:middle line:84%
of force interaction
that would make sense

00:18:32.360 --> 00:18:34.910 align:middle line:84%
to explain these
spacetime fields.

00:18:34.910 --> 00:18:36.500 align:middle line:90%
It's called tensegrity.

00:18:36.500 --> 00:18:38.780 align:middle line:84%
It's when something
is pushing apart

00:18:38.780 --> 00:18:42.230 align:middle line:84%
because it's vibrating
and also pulling together

00:18:42.230 --> 00:18:43.190 align:middle line:90%
in the same way.

00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:45.840 align:middle line:84%
Of course, he was thinking
about it architecturally.

00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:47.840 align:middle line:84%
Put this line over here
and this line over here.

00:18:47.840 --> 00:18:50.080 align:middle line:84%
And it has to have enough
of a push and pull.

