of something like this?

00:30:50.963 --> 00:30:51.880 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: Yeah, well--

00:30:51.880 --> 00:30:53.588 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: This doesn't
happen by accident.

00:30:53.588 --> 00:30:55.420 align:middle line:90%
>>APOLLO: That's right.

00:30:55.420 --> 00:30:57.940 align:middle line:84%
If you really get
down to it, you

00:30:57.940 --> 00:31:04.900 align:middle line:84%
realize that the whole
universe is extremely simple.

00:31:04.900 --> 00:31:07.520 align:middle line:84%
It's all trying to
get into balance.

00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:08.320 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:31:08.320 --> 00:31:09.153 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Constantly.

00:31:09.153 --> 00:31:11.810 align:middle line:84%
>>APOLLO: --if everything
is in balance already,

00:31:11.810 --> 00:31:13.670 align:middle line:90%
then you don't have anything.

00:31:13.670 --> 00:31:18.320 align:middle line:84%
And so you have to have things
a little bit off, a little bit

00:31:18.320 --> 00:31:22.250 align:middle line:84%
out of balance,
moving towards balance

00:31:22.250 --> 00:31:24.740 align:middle line:84%
in order to get
all the dynamics,

00:31:24.740 --> 00:31:26.060 align:middle line:90%
in order to get gravity.

00:31:26.060 --> 00:31:27.560 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as you
have gravity, you

00:31:27.560 --> 00:31:30.050 align:middle line:84%
have that five
spinning energy in.

00:31:30.050 --> 00:31:31.190 align:middle line:90%
Guess what?

00:31:31.190 --> 00:31:33.590 align:middle line:84%
Those extra points
that would make

00:31:33.590 --> 00:31:35.330 align:middle line:84%
